{{Infobox person | name = Saihei Hirose | image = Hirose Saihei.jpg | imagesize = | caption = | birth_date = June 16, 1828 | death_date = 1914 | birth_place = [[Shiga Prefecture]] | occupation = mining executive | networth = | spouse = | children = | residence = | alma_mater = | website = | signature = | footnotes =<ref name="Hirose">{{cite book|last=Hirose|first=Mitsumasa|title=宰平遺績 : 伝記・広瀬宰平 / 広瀬満正著 (Saihei iseki : denki Hirose Saihei)|publisher=Ōzorasha|location=Tokyo|date=2000, originally 1926|isbn=4-7568-0894-8|language=Japanese}}</ref> }}
'''Saihei Hirose''' (June 16, 1828 – 1914) was a [[Japanese people|Japanese]] [[mining]] businessman and former head of the board of directors of [[Sumitomo Group|Sumitomo Zaibatsu]] from 1877 to 1894.<ref name="Hirose"/> Prior to that, he was manager of the [[Besshi Copper Mine]], which he extensively modernised using Western technology.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sumitomo.gr.jp/english/history/history/index04.html|title=Development into a modern company after the Meiji era|work=History|publisher=Sumitomo Group Public Affairs Committee|accessdate=2009-04-20}}</ref><ref name="Wray">{{cite book|last=Wray|first=William D.|title=Mitsubishi and the N.Y.K., 1870-1914: business strategy in the Japanese shipping industry|publisher=Harvard Univ Asia Center|year=1984|edition=2nd|pages=139–141|chapter=Four|isbn=978-0-674-57665-0|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=QyMttnEyjiIC}}</ref>
There is a museum dedicated to him in [[Niihama]], called the Hirose Memorial Museum.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.city.niihama.lg.jp/english/museum.html|title=Hirose Memorial Museum|work=Welcome To Niihama: A Guidebook|publisher=Niihama City|accessdate=2009-04-20|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090422014005/http://www.city.niihama.lg.jp/english/museum.html|archivedate=2009-04-22|df=}}</ref>
