'''''The Adversity Paradox''''' is a business book written by [[J. Barry Griswell]] and [[Bob Jennings]]. Released in April 2009,<ref>[http://www.adversityparadox.com/ The Adversity Paradox] Retrieved on 2008-09-20</ref> the book was published by [[St. Martin’s Press]].<ref>[http://www.central.edu/news/story.cfm?ID=81 Central College] Central College News - Retrieved on 2008-09-21</ref> The book debuted at #8 on ''The Wall Street Journal'' Best Seller List.

''The Adversity Paradox'' is written as a guide for achieving personal and business success. The book explores the paradox of how many people from difficult and unstable backgrounds leverage adversity into success. Much of the book examines how readers can make adversity an asset instead of a liability.<ref>[http://www.agcia.info/schedule.asp The Associated General Contractors of Iowa]{{Dead link|date=June 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=no }} Convention 2009 - Retrieved on 2008-09-20</ref>

